Description: SpectralUnmix provides tools for spectral–spatial decomposition of
    hyperspectral datasets and integral field spectroscopy (IFU) cubes.
    The package implements spectral unmixing methods based on non-negative
    matrix factorization and related models to decompose a spectral cube
    into spatial abundance maps and spectral components.
    Optional spectral regularization can be applied to encourage smooth
    physically meaningful spectra.
